This message allows the delivery of GLONASS almanac assistance to a receiver. See thedescription of AssistNow Online for details.

column7: Payload
see below
Description
Message type (0x02 for this type)
Message version (0x00 for this version)
GLONASS Satellite identifier (see SatelliteNumbering)
Reserved
Reference calender day number of almanacwithin the four-year period (from string 5)
Type of GLONASS satellite (1 indicatesGLONASS-M)
Unhealthy flag at instant of almanac upload (1indicates operability of satellite)
Coarse time correction to GLONASS time
Eccentricity
Longitude of the first (within the N-day)ascending node of satellite orbit in PC-90.02coordinate system
Correction to the mean value of inclination
Time of the first ascending node passage
Correction to the mean value of Draconianperiod
Rate of change of Draconian perion
Carrier frequency number of navigation RFsignal, Range=(-7 .. 6)
Argument of perigee
Reserved
